  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package contains a future-dated evidence node (W-CON-03): the mesh-independence study report carries an evidenceTimestamp of 2027-03-15, which is strictly later than the package signatureTimestamp of 2024-11-20.",
